    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-25T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 25, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6651. Views expressed in Department’s 5604, November 7, 7 p.m., repeated to
                    Foreign Office and substance of Department’s 5924, November 24, 10 p.m.,
                    conveyed to it.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office states that it, too, feels that caution should be exercised,
                    particularly as wheat and currency problems are not definitely settled, and that
                    it has telegraphed British Minister at Tehran to this effect. In the same
                    telegram it has asked for fuller information regarding the charges against the
                    four prominent Iranians who the British authorities in Iran wish to arrest.
                    Foreign Office adds that <pb facs="0217" n="205" xml:id="pg_205"/> the possible
                    arrest of these individuals will be considered by it in the light of the
                    additional information that has been requested but that it hopes, in any event,
                    that it will not be necessary to take any action against the wishes of the
                    Iranian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
